o: Harvey Andrew Knibbs (born 26 April 1999) is an English professional footballer who plays for League Two club Cambridge United. Knibbs was born and raised in Derbyshire and joined the Nottingham Forest academy as a child before moving to Aston Villa. He signed his first professional contract at the end of the 2016–17 season. In June 2019 Knibbs signed a two-year contract with Cambridge United. On debut for Cambridge Knibbs scored the winning penalty as Championship side Brentford were defeated in the EFL Cup.
